node.text:
If you started your week off beer-prepping instead of meal-prepping, well, same! And lucky for all of us, our friends at @hopculturemag have some quick and easy beer-centric recipes to spice up your week. Like this Beer Cheese Dip! 🧀🍺

INGREDIENTS
1.5 cup cheddar cheese
1/2 cup mozzarella
8 oz. cream cheese
2 tsp garlic powder
1.5 tbsp Dijon mustard
1/4 cup beer (lager or IPA)

DIRECTIONS
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
2. In a medium bowl, combine cheddar cheese, mozzarella, cream cheese, garlic powder, and Dijon mustard and mash together until completely mixed
3. Add 1/4 cup of beer
4. Transfer to baking dish and bake until cheese bubbles
5. Enjoy with pretzels, tortilla chips, or veggies

Tag a friend you'd house this dip with.

node.title: How To Make Beer Cheese Dip with Hop Culture

📺 VIRTUAL HAPPY HOUR 📺 This Thursday, join us for a chat with Claudia Pamparana, co-owner of @factionbrewing, and Mike Shannon, National Director for @alesforals brewing program that benefits the ALS Therapy Development Institute (ALS TDI) developing treatments and therapies for ALS (Lou Gehrig’s Disease).

Along with breweries like @balebreaker, @russianriverbrewingofficial, @wormtownbrewery, @bellsbrewery, @harpoonbrewery, and many others, Faction has been part Ales for ALS program for over 9 years. Fun fact: Faction's very first beer was an Ales for ALS beer, released in September of 2013! Since 2014, Faction Brewing has hosted an annual Ales for ALS Brewfest, open to all participating breweries throughout California. 

Tune in for @hopcultureken’s chat with Claudia and Mike this Thursday at 7pm ET on YouTube. Don't forget to hit that subscribe button while you’re there! 💥

node.text:
Here’s something to really cheer about. This year Untappd has been proud to support @alesforals, a program that breweries from around the world have joined to help end ALS by crafting great beers. 

In 2013, co-owners of @balebreaker—Meghann Quinn, her husband Kevin Quinn, and Meghan’s brother Kevin Smith (known as “Smitty”)—helped start the Ales for ALS program with Mike and Cheryl Smith from @yakimachief and @loftusranches. Over the past seven years the program has helped raise over $3.5 million dollars for ALS research at the ALS Therapy Development Institute (@alstdi). On this very special episode of Drinking Socially Meghann and Smitty share their story and unveil a new badge “Drink to Ales for ALS”, earned by checking-in a beer from any of the participating breweries in the @alesforals program. To start we’re drinking Bubba’s Brew IPA 2021 from @balebreaker.

We're also shouting out @gansettbeer and @CounterWeightBrewingCo for crafting the best beers we had this week. Catch the latest episode on YouTube with the link in bio, or listen wherever you get your podcasts.
